Sentencas: A new SOFC cathode material, La1.98NiO4 +/-delta, was tested in presence of two electrolytes, yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) and gadolinia-doped ceria (GDC).
Titulo: La1.98NiO4±δ, a new cathode material for solid oxide fuel cell: Impedance spectroscopy study and compatibility with gadolinia-doped ceria and yttria-stabilized zirconia electrolytes

Sentencas: XRD analysis showed the absence of undesirable phases at the La1.98NiO4 +/-delta/GDC interface, whereas lanthanum zirconate (La2Zr2O7), an insulating phase, is present between electrode La1.98NiO4 +/-delta and YSz electrolyte.
Titulo: La1.98NiO4±δ, a new cathode material for solid oxide fuel cell: Impedance spectroscopy study and compatibility with gadolinia-doped ceria and yttria-stabilized zirconia electrolytes

Sentencas: XPS analysis showed that the oxygen lattice can be present in form of La-O and LaNiO3, which explains the high conductivity for these materials.
Titulo: La1.98NiO4±δ, a new cathode material for solid oxide fuel cell: Impedance spectroscopy study and compatibility with gadolinia-doped ceria and yttria-stabilized zirconia electrolytes

Sentencas: At temperatures lower than 650 degrees C, the area specific resistance of the electrodes, measured by electrochemical impedance spectroscopy is significantly inferior when associated to GDC rather than YSZ electrolyte.
Titulo: La1.98NiO4±δ, a new cathode material for solid oxide fuel cell: Impedance spectroscopy study and compatibility with gadolinia-doped ceria and yttria-stabilized zirconia electrolytes

Sentencas: In addition, in the case of GDC, a lower activation energy of about 0.7 eV was obtained, which could be explained by a higher mobility of oxide ions at the La1.98NiO4 +/-delta/GDC interface compared to the La1.98NiO4 +/-delta/YSZ one.
Titulo: La1.98NiO4±δ, a new cathode material for solid oxide fuel cell: Impedance spectroscopy study and compatibility with gadolinia-doped ceria and yttria-stabilized zirconia electrolytes
